ed in a \"decisions\" field of the JSON output. Verify that the returned structure has a non-empty \"decisions\" field and that the extracted decisions are present in that field, not in narrative sections. Confirm decisions are not duplicated across both fields.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The core failure here is in the segmentation and merging logic: the file is not split correctly, or the merged summary loses information, has duplication, or becomes incoherent. This can be caught at Integration level by testing the segmentation module, the processing pipeline (with mocked speech-to-text and LLM), and the merging module together. The failure of the real API or LLM to handle the merged context well is a secondary concern (Agentic/Workflow). Testing at Integration with a long transcript (>60 minutes) and mocks for external APIs is sufficient to catch core failure modes like incorrect splitting or broken merging logic.","test_description":"Create or load a multi-hour transcript (>60 minutes) with clear segment boundaries and distinct topics. Verify that the service splits it into segments (each ≤60 minutes). Mock the speech-to-text and LLM APIs to return realistic outputs for each segment (e.g., summaries with action items and decisions). Verify that segments are processed sequentially, and that the final merged summary: (1) contains all action items and decisions from all segments, (2) has no duplication, (3) is logically coherent without jarring context switches, and (4) preserves speaker attributions across segments.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output — completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior requires coordinating multiple agentic steps (speech-to-text transcription + LLM summarization) in sequence across real infrastructure (file upload/storage, API calls, output delivery). The failure modes span multiple concerns: API timeouts, network errors, partial failures at any stage, coordination issues between steps, or LLM non-determinism causing the pipeline to fail on some runs. A successful test requires executing the real pipeline end-to-end without mocks for the external services. This is a multi-step agentic workflow: each step depends on the prior one, and correctness depends on real LLM and external API behavior.","test_description":"Upload a real meeting recording or high-quality synthetic audio (at least 10–20 minutes, multi-speaker) to the service. Trigger the full pipeline: (1) file storage/retrieval, (2) speech-to-text API call, (3) LLM summarization, (4) structured output generation. Verify that all stages complete without errors, within expected time limits (no hangs/timeouts), and that the final structured summary is returned successfully. The output must be well-formed JSON with all expected fields (decisions, action items, attendees). Run the test multiple times (at least 5) to account for transient failures and LLM non-determinism. The test passes only if the pipeline completes successfully on all runs.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.62}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13388,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13388},"output_tokens":4,"se